#: ../../source/library/models/epidemics/SWIR.rst:4
#: b660e6e4be9c4f12a920c0024a65f90c
msgid "The SWIR Model [1]_ extends the classic SIR framework by introducing a **Weakened (W)** state between Susceptible (S) and Infected (I). Infection spreads only through links between neighboring nodes in a graph :math:`G=(V,E)`. Each node is in one of four states: :math:`S` (susceptible), :math:`W` (weakened), :math:`I` (infected), or :math:`R` (recovered). At a high level, a susceptible node can either be weakened or directly infected by its infected neighbors; weakened nodes can subsequently become infected; infected nodes recover and become immune (R). The model is parameterized by three per-contact rates: :math:`\\kappa` (direct infection), :math:`\\mu` (weakening), and :math:`\\nu` (weak-to-infected)."
msgstr ""

